# PURPOSE

This document is the authoritative roadmap and release journal for
Project Atlas.

Every implementation prompt, development task, architecture decision,
feature request, release decision, and engineering milestone must align
with this document.

This file is updated after every development session so Atlas always has
a single source of truth regardless of chat history.

This document exists to:

• Keep development organized.

• Prevent duplicate work.

• Preserve architectural consistency.

• Track completed milestones.

• Record engineering decisions.

• Prioritize release-critical work.

• Prevent loss of project context.

• Serve as the permanent development journal until Version 1.0.

====================================================================
# PRODUCT VISION

Atlas is an autonomous AI Operating System for inventors.

Atlas is NOT:

• a chatbot

• a project management application

• another AI assistant

Atlas behaves like an autonomous company.

Specialized AI departments perform real work.

Departments communicate with one another.

Departments create structured outputs.

Departments automatically continue work whenever dependencies are satisfied.

The founder only participates when Atlas reaches a real-world approval
boundary.

The long-term objective is for Atlas to transform an invention from idea
to manufacturing-ready product with minimal founder intervention.

====================================================================
# PRODUCT PRINCIPLES

These principles are permanent.

1. Atlas performs work instead of giving advice.

2. Atlas owns every task it can reasonably complete.

3. Human interaction should only occur when legally, strategically,
financially, or physically required.

4. Every department produces measurable outputs.

5. Every completed output becomes structured input for downstream
departments.

6. Atlas automatically continues work whenever dependencies are satisfied.

7. Engineering decisions always take priority over cosmetic decisions.

8. Native architecture is preferred over third-party dependence.

9. One source of truth for every piece of information.

10. No duplicated workspaces.

11. No duplicated execution.

12. No duplicated packages.

13. Progressive disclosure will replace information overload during
post-autonomy UI refinement.

