====================================================================
# TASK IMPLEMENTATION RULES

Every implementation task must follow these rules without exception.

------------------------------------------------------------

1. Preserve Existing Architecture

Never rewrite working systems simply to improve style or organization.

Favor extending existing architecture over replacing it.

------------------------------------------------------------

2. One Milestone at a Time

Only implement the currently active milestone.

Do not begin work on future milestones until the current milestone is
fully completed, verified, and deployed.

------------------------------------------------------------

3. Backward Compatibility

New functionality must never break existing founder workflows,
department interactions, or saved data.

------------------------------------------------------------

4. Autonomous First

When choosing between:

• UI improvements

• New autonomous capabilities

always prioritize autonomous capability until Version 1.0 is complete.

------------------------------------------------------------

5. CEO Visibility

Every major autonomous action must be visible through the CEO Command
Center with an understandable status and outcome.

------------------------------------------------------------

6. Explainability

Atlas must always be able to explain:

• what it is doing,

• why it is doing it,

• what evidence supports the decision,

• and what happens next.

------------------------------------------------------------

7. Human Approval

Human approval should only be requested when required for:

• legal decisions,

• financial commitments,

• external communication,

• irreversible actions,

or when explicitly configured by the founder.

------------------------------------------------------------

8. Regression Testing

Every completed milestone must include:

✓ Unit tests

✓ Integration tests

✓ TypeScript validation

✓ Production build

✓ Deployment verification

